text: Tomas Aguon Camacho (September 18, 1933 â€“ March 5, 2018) was a Northern Mariana Islander religious figure. He was the first Bishop of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Chalan Kanoa in the Northern Mariana Islands. He served as bishop from 1984 until his retirement in 2010. He was born in Chalan Kanoa, Saipan. Camacho died in Saipan on March 5, 2018 of sepsis, aged 84. ==References== Category:1933 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Deaths from sepsis Category:Northern Mariana Islands Category:Roman Catholic bishops
